column18: Combined score for Social Reference scale
extent to which subject believed dictator was motivated by desire to earn more money
extent to which subject believed dictator wanted to reduce their bonus
describes whether the dictator game was a giving game or a taking game
describes whether the subject's partner made a fair or stingy decision
the extent to which subject believed the other players in the game were real (1 = very skeptical that other player was real; 5 = very confident that other player was real)
describes whether a subject has previously participated in a task like this before (1 = nothing like this scenario; 5 = exactly like this scenario)
codes subjects role as a second-party receiver or third-party bystander
